    "title": "Creating a Social Media Content Calendar for UK Brands",
    "excerpt": "Plan and execute a social media content calendar that keeps your UK audience engaged.",
    "content": "## Why You Need a Content Calendar\n\nA content calendar is the backbone of an effective social media strategy. It ensures consistency, reduces last-minute scrambling, and allows you to align your content with important dates, events, and campaigns. For UK brands, a well-planned calendar accounts for local holidays, cultural events, and seasonal business trends.\n\n## Building Your Calendar\n\nMap out important UK dates including public holidays, cultural festivals, and industry-specific events. Plan a content mix that follows the 80-20 rule: 80% value-driven content that educates, entertains, or inspires, and 20% promotional content. Use scheduling tools like Buffer or Hootsuite to automate posting. Leave room for real-time content to capitalize on trending topics. Review and adjust your calendar monthly based on performance data and audience feedback.",
