    "title": "How to Perform an SEO Audit for Your UK Website",
    "excerpt": "Conduct a comprehensive SEO audit to identify issues and opportunities for UK websites.",
    "content": "## The Importance of Regular SEO Audits\n\nYour website's SEO health directly impacts your visibility in search results. Regular audits help you identify technical issues, content gaps, and optimization opportunities before they harm your rankings. For UK businesses competing in local search, staying on top of SEO maintenance is critical.\n\n## Audit Checklist\n\nReview your technical SEO: check crawlability, indexation status, site speed, mobile-friendliness, and core web vitals. Analyze your on-page SEO: evaluate title tags, meta descriptions, heading structure, and keyword optimization. Assess your content quality: identify thin content, duplicate content, and opportunities for expansion. Review your backlink profile for toxic links that could trigger penalties. Check your local SEO: verify NAP consistency, Google Business Profile optimization, and local citation accuracy. Use tools like Google Search Console, Google Analytics, SEMrush, and Screaming Frog to gather data. Document findings and create a prioritized action plan.",
