    "excerpt": "Avoid these frequent local SEO pitfalls that are hurting your visibility in the UK search results.",
    "content": "## Mistakes That Cost You Rankings\n\nMany London businesses unknowingly make local SEO mistakes that undermine their search visibility. These errors range from technical oversights to strategic missteps, but all of them can be fixed with awareness and effort.\n\n## Most Common Mistakes\n\nInconsistent NAP information across online directories confuses Google and harms your local rankings. Neglecting your Google Business Profile by not completing all fields or failing to respond to reviews signals a lack of engagement. Using the wrong business categories on your GBP limits your visibility for relevant searches. Ignoring mobile optimization sends away the majority of London searchers. Having no local content strategy means missing opportunities to rank for neighborhood-specific searches. Failing to build local citations and backlinks from UK websites limits your authority signals. Not tracking local rankings means you cannot measure your progress or identify areas for improvement.",
