    "slug": "measuring-roi-digital-marketing-campaigns",
    "title": "How to Measure ROI on Your Digital Marketing Campaigns",
    "excerpt": "A practical guide to calculating and improving the return on investment of your digital marketing efforts.",
    "content": "## Why ROI Measurement Matters\n\nMany UK businesses invest heavily in digital marketing without a clear system for measuring returns. Without proper ROI tracking, you risk wasting budget on channels that don't convert. Understanding which campaigns drive real business value is the difference between guessing and growing.\n\n## Key Metrics to Track\n\nFocus on metrics that tie directly to business goals. For e-commerce, track cost per acquisition (CPA) and return on ad spend (ROAS). For lead generation, monitor cost per lead and conversion rate. For brand awareness, measure engagement rate and share of voice. Google Analytics 4, Meta Business Suite, and call tracking tools like CallRail can help attribute conversions to specific campaigns.\n\n## Calculating Your ROI\n\nThe basic formula is: (Revenue Generated - Cost of Campaign) / Cost of Campaign x 100. For example, if you spent �500,000 on a Google Ads campaign and generated �2,000,000 in revenue, your ROI is 300%. Track this monthly and compare across channels. Use UTM parameters religiously and set up conversion tracking before launching any campaign. Without proper tracking, you are flying blind.",
