    "slug": "email-marketing-strategies-nigerian-businesses",
    "title": "Email Marketing Strategies That Work for UK Businesses",
    "excerpt": "Unlock the power of email marketing with strategies tailored for the UK market and audience.",
    "content": "## Why Email Still Matters\n\nWith over 65 million internet users in the UK, email remains one of the highest ROI marketing channels. Despite the rise of social media, email delivers an average ROI of �3,800 for every �100 spent. Unlike social platforms where algorithms control reach, your email list is an asset you own. For London businesses, email is especially effective for B2B outreach, appointment reminders, and abandoned cart recovery.\n\n## Building and Segmenting Your List\n\nStart with lead magnets relevant to UK audiences — free guides on topics like \"10 Ways to Save on Business Taxes\" or discount codes for first purchases. Use tools like Mailchimp or Sendinblue to segment your list by location, purchase history, and engagement level. A London-based fashion brand might send different campaigns to customers in Shoreditch versus those in Canary Wharf. Segmentation can increase open rates by 60% and click-through rates by 100%.\n\n## Crafting Emails That Convert\n\nUK audiences respond well to personalized, value-driven content. Write subject lines that create curiosity or urgency — \"Last chance: 20% off London delivery ends Friday\" outperforms generic alternatives. Optimize for mobile since over 70% of emails in the UK are opened on phones. Test send times — data shows that Tuesday and Thursday mornings around 10 AM GMT yield the best open rates for UK subscribers.",
