    "title": "Why Custom Websites Matter for UK Businesses in 2026",
    "excerpt": "Discover why off-the-shelf templates are holding your business back and how custom websites drive real growth.",
    "content": "## The Problem with Template Websites\n\nMany UK businesses opt for cheap template websites or DIY site builders, but these solutions come with hidden costs. Templates are often bloated with unused code, slow to load, and difficult to customize. In a market where 53% of mobile users abandon sites that take longer than 3 seconds to load, a slow template site is costing you customers. More importantly, template sites lack the SEO structure needed to rank on Google the UK.\n\n## Benefits of a Custom-Built Site\n\nA custom website is built specifically for your business goals. Need a multi-vendor marketplace or a booking system integrated with Stripe? A custom solution handles it seamlessly. Custom sites also perform better on Core Web Vitals, which Google uses as a ranking factor. Security is another critical advantage — custom code is less likely to have vulnerabilities that hackers exploit, a growing concern for London e-commerce businesses.\n\n## Long-Term Value\n\nWhile a custom website requires a larger upfront investment, the long-term returns far outweigh the cost. You avoid monthly fees for plugins and templates, you can scale without rebuilding, and your site becomes a genuine asset that appreciates in value. Boyzeth Solutions has helped dozens of London businesses migrate from templates to custom builds, with clients reporting 40-60% improvements in page speed and 25% increases in conversion rates.",
