    "slug": "website-performance-optimization-guide",
    "title": "Website Performance Optimization: A Complete Guide for UK Businesses",
    "excerpt": "Speed matters. Learn how to optimize your website for faster load times and better user experience in the UK.",
    "content": "## Why Speed Matters in the UK\n\nInternet infrastructure in the UK varies widely — from fiber in Canary Wharf to 3G in rural areas. A website that loads instantly on a fast connection might take 10 seconds on a slower network. Studies show that 53% of UK mobile users will abandon a site that takes over 3 seconds to load. For e-commerce sites, every second of delay costs an average of 7% in conversions. Speed directly impacts your bottom line.\n\n## Optimization Techniques\n\nStart with image optimization — compress JPEGs to 80% quality and use WebP format. Implement lazy loading so images below the fold load only when needed. Minimize HTTP requests by combining CSS and JavaScript files. Use a content delivery network (CDN) like Cloudflare to cache your site across global servers. Enable Gzip compression and leverage browser caching. For WordPress sites, choose lightweight themes and limit plugins to essentials.\n\n## Tools and Monitoring\n\nUse Google PageSpeed Insights, GTmetrix, and WebPageTest to audit your site. Aim for a mobile score of 90+ on PageSpeed Insights. Monitor Core Web Vitals — Largest Contentful Paint (LCP) should be under 2.5 seconds, First Input Delay (FID) under 100ms, and Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS) under 0.1. Regular performance audits should be part of your maintenance routine. A fast website is the foundation of good SEO and user experience.",
