    "slug": "technical-seo-guide-nigerian-websites",
    "title": "Technical SEO: The Foundation of Search Engine Success in the UK",
    "excerpt": "Learn the technical SEO essentials that help UK websites get found, crawled, and ranked by Google.",
    "content": "## Why Technical SEO Matters\n\nTechnical SEO ensures that search engines can crawl, index, and understand your website. Without a solid technical foundation, even the best content won't rank. In the UK, where hosting quality and site speed vary dramatically, technical SEO can give you a significant competitive advantage. Google's crawlers need to access your site efficiently, and technical issues can prevent them from discovering your content.\n\n## Key Technical Elements\n\nStart with site architecture — create an XML sitemap and submit it to Google Search Console. Ensure your robots.txt file isn't blocking important pages. Implement canonical tags to prevent duplicate content issues. Use structured data markup (schema.org) to help Google understand your content and enable rich snippets in search results. For London businesses, LocalBusiness schema with address, phone, and opening hours is particularly valuable.\n\n## Monitoring and Maintenance\n\nRegularly check Google Search Console for crawl errors, manual actions, and index coverage issues. Monitor your site's Core Web Vitals — these are now ranking factors. Fix broken links using tools like Screaming Frog. Ensure your site is HTTPS — Google flags non-HTTPS sites as not secure, which hurts both rankings and user trust. Schedule quarterly technical SEO audits to catch issues early and maintain your search visibility.",
