    "slug": "seo-audit-guide-for-websites",
    "title": "How to Conduct an SEO Audit for Your UK Business Website",
    "excerpt": "A step-by-step guide to performing a comprehensive SEO audit and identifying opportunities for improvement.",
    "content": "## What is an SEO Audit?\n\nAn SEO audit is a comprehensive evaluation of your website's search engine performance. It identifies technical issues, content gaps, and optimization opportunities. For UK businesses, regular SEO audits are essential because search behavior and Google's algorithms evolve constantly. A thorough audit should be conducted at least every quarter.\n\n## Steps to Audit Your Site\n\nStart with a technical audit using Google Search Console — check for crawl errors, index coverage, and mobile usability issues. Use PageSpeed Insights to evaluate site speed. Review your on-page elements — title tags, meta descriptions, and header tags should all be optimized. Analyze your content for quality, relevance, and keyword targeting. Check your backlink profile using Ahrefs or SEMrush. Finally, evaluate your competitors to identify gaps and opportunities.\n\n## Creating an Action Plan\n\nPrioritize issues by impact. Fix critical technical problems like broken links and slow pages first. Update outdated content and optimize pages that are underperforming. Identify quick wins — pages ranking on page 2 of Google that can be pushed to page 1 with minor optimizations. Set measurable goals for each audit cycle. Track progress using Google Analytics and Search Console. A systematic approach to SEO audits ensures continuous improvement and sustained search visibility.",
