    "title": "Facebook Advertising in the UK: A Complete Guide for Business Owners",
    "excerpt": "Master Facebook Ads to reach UK customers effectively and maximize your advertising budget.",
    "content": "## Facebook's Reach in the UK\n\nFacebook remains the largest social platform in the UK with over 35 million users. Despite competition from newer platforms, Facebook's sophisticated advertising tools and massive user base make it indispensable for UK businesses. The platform's targeting capabilities allow you to reach specific demographics, interests, and behaviors with precision.\n\n## Setting Up Campaigns That Convert\n\nStart with a clear objective — brand awareness, lead generation, or conversions. For London businesses, location targeting is crucial. Target specific boroughs — Shoreditch, Camden, Canary Wharf, Kensington — and set a radius. Use interest targeting to reach people interested in your industry. Create lookalike audiences from your existing customer list for higher conversion rates. The Facebook Pixel is essential for tracking conversions and building retargeting audiences.\n\n## Budget Optimization Tips\n\nStart with a daily budget of �3,000-�5,000 per ad set. Test 3-4 different creatives simultaneously and let Facebook optimize toward the best performer. Run ads during peak hours — evening hours (6 PM-10 PM GMT) and weekends typically see higher engagement. Monitor your cost per result closely. A good cost per click (CPC) in the UK ranges from �100-�300 depending on industry. Scale winning ad sets gradually — increase budget by no more than 20% every 3 days to maintain performance stability.",
