    "title": "How to Create a Social Media Content Calendar for Your UK Business",
    "excerpt": "Stay organized and consistent with a social media content calendar tailored to the UK audience.",
    "content": "## Why a Content Calendar Matters\n\nConsistency is the secret to social media success, and a content calendar is your roadmap. Without one, you post sporadically, miss important dates, and struggle to maintain quality. UK businesses that use content calendars report 60% higher engagement and 40% less time spent on daily social media management. A calendar also helps you align your content with business goals and seasonal events.\n\n## Building Your Calendar\n\nStart by mapping out UK holidays and events — Independence Day, Sallah, Christmas, Easter, and local festivals like Eyo or Calabar Carnival. Plan content themes for each month. For example, January might focus on New Year promotions, August on back-to-school campaigns. Use a tool like Google Sheets, Notion, or Later. Include columns for platform, content type (carousel, video, image), caption, hashtags, and publishing date.\n\n## Content Mix and Scheduling\n\nFollow the 80/20 rule — 80% value-driven content and 20% promotional. Value content includes tips, industry insights, behind-the-scenes, and user-generated content. Schedule posts during peak engagement times — 12 PM-2 PM and 7 PM-9 PM GMT on weekdays. Use scheduling tools like Buffer or Meta Business Suite to automate posting. Review your calendar weekly and adjust based on performance. A living calendar that evolves with trends and audience feedback will serve you better than a rigid plan.",
