    "slug": "content-repurposing-strategies",
    "title": "Maximize Your Content: A Guide to Content Repurposing for UK Marketers",
    "excerpt": "Learn how to repurpose your content across multiple platforms to save time and reach a wider audience.",
    "content": "## Why Repurpose Content?\n\nCreating fresh content daily is exhausting and inefficient. Content repurposing — taking one piece of content and adapting it for different platforms — solves this problem. A single blog post can become an Instagram carousel, a LinkedIn article, a YouTube video script, a Twitter thread, and an email newsletter. This approach saves time, reinforces your message across channels, and reaches people who prefer different content formats.\n\n## A Practical Repurposing Workflow\n\nStart with a cornerstone piece — a detailed guide, research report, or comprehensive blog post. Extract key points for social media carousels. Turn statistics into infographics using Canva. Record a short video summarizing the main points for Instagram Reels or TikTok. Write a LinkedIn post highlighting key takeaways. Create a Twitter thread with the most impactful quotes. Send a summarized version to your email list. One week of work can produce a month of content across all platforms.\n\n## Tools to Streamline the Process\n\nUse Canva for visual content creation, Otter.ai for transcribing videos into text, and Headli for turning blog posts into social media captions. Schedule repurposed content using Buffer or Later. Track which repurposed formats perform best on each platform. Data from UK businesses shows that repurposed content generates 60-70% of the engagement of original content while requiring 80% less production time. Repurposing is not about cutting corners — it is about working smarter.",
