    "title": "Customer Acquisition Strategies That Work for UK Businesses",
    "excerpt": "Learn proven customer acquisition channels and techniques to grow your UK business sustainably.",
    "content": "## Understanding Acquisition Costs\n\nCustomer acquisition cost (CAC) is one of the most important metrics for any business. In the UK, CAC varies dramatically by industry and channel. A London-based SaaS company might spend �50,000 to acquire a customer through Google Ads, while a restaurant might acquire customers for �500 through Instagram. Understanding your CAC across different channels allows you to allocate your marketing budget effectively.\n\n## Top Acquisition Channels in the UK\n\nSocial media advertising — particularly Instagram and Facebook — remains the most accessible channel for UK businesses. Google Ads captures high-intent users actively searching for your products. Referral programs work exceptionally well in the UK's relationship-driven culture. Partner with micro-influencers whose audiences match your target demographic. Content marketing through blog posts and YouTube videos builds organic traffic over time. WhatsApp Business is an underutilized acquisition channel — broadcast messages and status updates reach customers directly.\n\n## Optimizing Your Funnel\n\nMap your customer journey from awareness to purchase. Create targeted content for each stage — educational content for awareness, comparison guides for consideration, and testimonials for decision. Use retargeting to bring back visitors who left without converting. A/B test landing pages, ad copy, and calls-to-action. Track conversion rates at each stage and identify drop-off points. Continuous optimization of your acquisition funnel reduces CAC and improves ROI across all marketing channels.",
