    "slug": "google-ads-for-nigerian-businesses",
    "title": "Google Ads for UK Businesses: A Complete Beginner's Guide",
    "excerpt": "Master Google Ads to capture high-intent customers searching for your products or services in the UK.",
    "content": "## Why Google Ads Works in the UK\n\nWhen UK consumers need a product or service, they search Google. Over 90% of market share belongs to Google in the UK, making it the dominant search engine. Google Ads allows you to appear at the top of search results for keywords relevant to your business. Unlike social media ads that interrupt users, Google Ads captures people who are actively looking for what you offer — this intent makes it one of the highest-converting advertising channels.\n\n## Setting Up Your First Campaign\n\nStart with Search campaigns targeting the UK. Choose keywords with commercial intent — \"web design company London\" converts better than \"what is web design.\" Use match types — exact match for high-intent terms, phrase match for broader reach. Structure your account by theme — separate campaigns for different services or products. Set a daily budget you are comfortable with — �5,000 is a good starting point. Write ad copy that includes your keyword, a unique selling proposition, and a clear call-to-action.\n\n## Optimization and Scaling\n\nMonitor key metrics — click-through rate (CTR), conversion rate, cost per conversion, and quality score. A good CTR in the UK is 3-5%. Improve quality score by creating relevant ad groups, optimizing landing pages, and including keywords in ad copy. Use ad extensions — sitelinks, callouts, and call extensions — to improve visibility. Add negative keywords to exclude irrelevant searches. Review search terms reports weekly to identify new opportunities and wasteful spend. Scale campaigns that achieve your target cost per acquisition.",
