    "slug": "facebook-ads-budget-optimization",
    "title": "Facebook Ads Budget Optimization: Get More From Every Naira",
    "excerpt": "Optimize your Facebook Ads budget to maximize results and reduce wasted spend in the UK market.",
    "content": "## The Challenge of Ad Spend in the UK\n\nWith rising CPM costs on Facebook, UK advertisers need to be more strategic than ever. A campaign that worked six months ago might now cost twice as much per result. Budget optimization is not about spending less — it is about spending smarter. Every Pound wasted on poorly targeted or poorly optimized campaigns is money that could be generating sales.\n\n## Budget Optimization Strategies\n\nStart with proper campaign structure. Use the CBO (Campaign Budget Optimization) feature — let Facebook automatically distribute budget across your best-performing ad sets. Test audiences systematically — create 3-5 ad sets with different targeting and let Facebook optimize toward the best. Use minimum ROAS bid strategies for conversion campaigns. Set frequency caps — if the same person sees your ad more than 4 times without converting, show them something different or stop.\n\n## Creative and Audience Management\n\nRefresh creative every 2-3 weeks to prevent ad fatigue. Test 3-4 different creative variations in each ad set — different images, copy angles, and formats. Create audiences based on engagement — retarget people who watched 50% of your video or clicked your link. Exclude converted customers from prospecting campaigns. Review placement performance — sometimes limiting to Instagram Feed alone outperforms automatic placements. Run ads during peak hours and pause underperforming ad sets immediately. Regular optimization can reduce cost per result by 30-50%.",
