    "slug": "retargeting-strategies-nigerian-brands",
    "title": "Retargeting Strategies That Recover Lost Customers for UK Brands",
    "excerpt": "Bring back website visitors who left without converting using proven retargeting techniques.",
    "content": "## Why Retargeting is Essential\n\nStudies show that 97% of website visitors leave without converting on their first visit. In the UK, where trust-building takes time, first-visit conversions are even rarer. Retargeting allows you to stay top-of-mind and bring these visitors back when they are ready to buy. Retargeted visitors are 70% more likely to convert than new visitors, making it one of the highest-ROI advertising strategies.\n\n## Setting Up Retargeting Campaigns\n\nInstall the Meta Pixel or Google Ads tag on your website to build audience lists. Create segmented audiences based on behavior — people who visited pricing pages, added items to cart, or spent more than 30 seconds on your site. For each segment, create tailored ads that address their specific stage in the buying journey. Someone who abandoned their cart needs a reminder with a possible discount. Someone who read a blog post needs more educational content.\n\n## Best Practices for UK Campaigns\n\nSet frequency caps — 3-5 impressions per person per day is ideal. Use dynamic product ads for e-commerce — show users exactly what they viewed. Create urgency with limited-time offers — \"UK Independence Sale ends Friday.\" Test different ad formats — carousel ads showcasing multiple products perform well for retargeting. Exclude recent converters from your retargeting lists. Track lift in overall conversion rate and return on ad spend. A well-executed retargeting strategy can increase overall conversion rates by 20-30%.",
