    "slug": "ppc-campaign-management-nigeria",
    "title": "PPC Campaign Management: A Guide for UK Advertisers",
    "excerpt": "Everything you need to know about managing successful pay-per-click campaigns for the UK market.",
    "content": "## The Foundations of PPC Management\n\nPay-per-click (PPC) advertising is one of the fastest ways to drive targeted traffic to your website. However, without proper management, PPC campaigns can quickly drain your budget. Successful PPC management requires ongoing attention to keywords, bids, ad copy, landing pages, and audience targeting. For UK businesses, the key is balancing competition — high-volume keywords in London cost more but convert better.\n\n## Daily and Weekly Management Tasks\n\nCheck campaign performance daily for the first week after launch. Monitor for unusual spikes in cost or drops in conversion rate. Review search term reports to add new keywords and add negative keywords. Check impression share — if it is below 50%, consider increasing budget or improving quality score. Pause underperforming ad groups. Test new ad copy variations weekly. Set up automated rules to pause ads if cost per conversion exceeds your threshold.\n\n## Advanced Management Strategies\n\nUse dayparting to show ads during peak hours only — for most UK businesses, 8 AM to 10 PM GMT is optimal. Create audience layering — target users who are in your retargeting list AND searching for your keywords. Use RLSA (Remarketing Lists for Search Ads) to bid differently for returning visitors. Implement call tracking to measure phone call conversions. Schedule monthly performance reviews with a focus on trends rather than daily fluctuations. Proper PPC management is the difference between a campaign that loses money and one that scales profitably.",
