    "slug": "gbp-post-creation-nigeria",
    "title": "Google Business Profile Posts: How to Create Engaging Updates for UK Customers",
    "excerpt": "Leverage GBP posts to engage customers, promote offers, and improve your local search visibility.",
    "content": "## What Are GBP Posts?\n\nGoogle Business Profile posts are updates that appear directly in your business listing on Google Search and Maps. These posts allow you to share offers, events, product highlights, and blog content with potential customers exactly when they find your business. For UK businesses, GBP posts are an underutilized tool that can significantly improve engagement and local search performance.\n\n## Types of Posts and Best Practices\n\nThere are four types of GBP posts — what's new, offers, events, and products. What's new posts are great for sharing updates, behind-the-scenes content, and industry tips. Offer posts drive sales by promoting discounts or special deals. Event posts promote workshops, sales, or openings. Product posts showcase specific items with descriptions and prices. For maximum impact, include high-quality images or short videos, write compelling headlines, and include clear calls-to-action.\n\n## Posting Schedule and Optimization\n\nPost at least once per week to maintain an active profile. Google favors recently updated profiles in local search rankings. Promote seasonal offers — Sallah sales, Independence Day promotions, Christmas deals. Share customer testimonials as posts. Link posts to relevant landing pages on your website. Track post performance through GBP insights — views, clicks, and actions. Analyze which types of posts generate the most engagement and adjust your strategy accordingly. Consistent posting keeps your profile fresh and signals relevance to Google's algorithm.",
