    "slug": "google-business-profile-insights-analysis",
    "title": "How to Analyze Google Business Profile Insights for Better Local SEO",
    "excerpt": "Understand the data behind your Google Business Profile and use insights to improve your local marketing.",
    "content": "## Understanding GBP Insights\n\nGoogle Business Profile provides powerful analytics about how customers find and interact with your listing. These insights include how customers searched for you (direct, discovery, or branded), where they found you (Search or Maps), and what actions they took (website visits, direction requests, phone calls). For London businesses, this data is invaluable for understanding local customer behavior.\n\n## Key Metrics to Track\n\nMonitor views — how many times your profile appears in search results. Track the split between Search views (people searching for your category) and Maps views (people navigating to your location). Check the actions metrics — website clicks, direction requests, and phone calls. Analyze the search queries report to see exactly what terms people used to find you. Identify which photos or posts drive the most engagement. Track these metrics monthly to establish baselines and measure improvement.\n\n## Using Insights to Improve\n\nIf most searches are discovery-based (people finding you while searching for your category), focus on category optimization and keyword-rich descriptions. If phone calls are your highest action, ensure your phone number is prominent and your call center is staffed during peak hours. If direction requests are low, your location might be hard to find — add more photos of your exterior and nearby landmarks. Use search query data to identify new keywords for your website and GBP description. Regular analysis of insights leads to data-driven decisions that improve your local search performance over time.",
