    "slug": "gbp-review-management-nigeria",
    "title": "Mastering Review Management on Google Business Profile for UK Brands",
    "excerpt": "Learn how to manage, respond to, and leverage customer reviews to build trust and improve local rankings.",
    "content": "## The Power of Reviews in the UK\n\nOnline reviews are the digital equivalent of word-of-mouth marketing in the UK. Before visiting a new restaurant or hiring a service, most London consumers check Google reviews. A business with a 4.5-star rating and 100 reviews will almost always be chosen over a competitor with no reviews. Reviews directly impact your local search ranking — Google considers review quantity, recency, and sentiment as ranking factors.\n\n## Best Practices for Review Management\n\nAsk happy customers to leave reviews — send a follow-up email or WhatsApp message with a direct link to your GBP review page. Never offer incentives for reviews — Google prohibits this and could penalize your listing. Respond to every review within 24-48 hours. Thank positive reviewers personally — mention something specific from their experience. For negative reviews, respond professionally and offer to resolve the issue offline. A well-handled negative review can actually build more trust than ignoring it.\n\n## Leveraging Reviews for Growth\n\nFeature positive reviews in your social media posts and website testimonials. Use review insights to identify areas for improvement — if multiple reviews mention slow service, address it. Flag fake reviews through Google's support system. Monitor your review velocity — a sudden drop in new reviews might indicate an issue. Aim for a steady stream of reviews rather than sporadic bursts. UK businesses that actively manage reviews see 20% higher ratings and significantly more customer inquiries than those that do not.",
