    "slug": "local-search-ranking-factors-nigeria",
    "title": "Local Search Ranking Factors: What Matters for UK Businesses",
    "excerpt": "Understand the key factors that determine local search rankings and improve your visibility on Google.",
    "content": "## The Local Search Algorithm\n\nGoogle's local search algorithm uses three main categories: relevance, distance, and prominence. Relevance measures how well your business matches what the user searched for. Distance considers the proximity of your business to the searcher's location. Prominence evaluates how well-known and authoritative your business is. For UK businesses, understanding these factors is the first step to improving local search rankings.\n\n## Top Ranking Factors for 2026\n\nGoogle Business Profile completeness remains the single most important factor — verified profiles with complete information, photos, and regular posts rank highest. Online reviews — quantity, recency, and average rating — are the second most important factor. Local citations with consistent NAP information follow. On-page signals like location-specific content, title tags with city names, and embedded Google Maps on your website also contribute. Backlinks from local UK websites and directories boost prominence.\n\n## Practical Improvement Steps\n\nAudit your GBP and ensure every field is complete. Launch a review generation campaign — aim for 5-10 new reviews monthly. Build 10-15 local citations focusing on UK directories. Create location-specific content on your website. Earn backlinks from local organizations, event pages, and partners. Monitor your local search performance using Google Search Console and third-party tools. Local SEO is an ongoing process — businesses that consistently work on these factors maintain and improve their rankings over time.",
