    "slug": "review-management-strategies-nigeria",
    "title": "Online Review Management Strategies for UK Service Businesses",
    "excerpt": "Build a stellar online reputation through strategic review management tailored for UK businesses.",
    "content": "## The Impact of Reviews on UK Businesses\n\nOnline reviews influence 93% of purchasing decisions in the UK. A single negative review can cost you dozens of customers, while a strong collection of positive reviews can make your business the default choice in your category. For London service businesses — restaurants, salons, clinics, and agencies — reviews are often the deciding factor between two otherwise similar options.\n\n## Proactive Review Generation\n\nAsk for reviews at the peak of customer satisfaction — immediately after a successful delivery or positive interaction. Make it easy by sending a direct link via WhatsApp or SMS. Train your staff to request reviews at the right moment. Offer exceptional service that naturally inspires reviews — surprise upgrades, follow-up calls, personalized touches. Target specific review platforms — Google for local businesses, Instagram for creative services, LinkedIn for B2B services.\n\n## Handling Negative Feedback\n\nRespond to negative reviews within 24 hours. Always start by apologizing for their experience, even if you believe the complaint is unwarranted. Take the conversation offline — offer to discuss via phone or direct message. Address specific concerns and explain how you will prevent similar issues. A thoughtful response to a negative review shows potential customers that you care about service quality. Monitor review patterns — if multiple customers mention the same issue, fix it. Proactive review management builds a reputation that attracts customers and deters competitors.",
