    "title": "TikTok Ads for UK Businesses: Getting Started Guide",
    "excerpt": "Learn how to advertise on TikTok to reach the UK's fastest-growing social media audience.",
    "content": "## Why TikTok Ads in the UK?\n\nTikTok's advertising platform has matured significantly, offering sophisticated targeting and ad formats. With over 15 million active UK users, the platform provides access to a young, engaged audience that is increasingly difficult to reach on traditional platforms. TikTok's algorithm-driven feed means your ads can reach users beyond your followers, maximizing your ad spend efficiency.\n\n## Ad Formats and Best Practices\n\nIn-Feed Ads appear in users' For You feeds and support various call-to-action options. Spark Ads allow you to boost organic posts from your account or creator partners, making them feel more native. Branded Hashtag Challenges encourage user-generated content and massive engagement. For UK advertisers, In-Feed and Spark Ads are the most accessible starting points. Use vertical video with strong hooks in the first 2 seconds. Authentic, raw content outperforms polished productions.\n\n## Targeting and Optimization\n\nTarget by location — the UK, specific cities, or radius targeting. Use interest and behavior targeting to reach users interested in your industry. Create lookalike audiences from your customer data. Set a daily budget starting from $10 (approximately �7,000-�8,000). Monitor cost per mille (CPM) and cost per click (CPC) — UK TikTok CPMs are generally lower than Facebook. Test multiple creatives and let the algorithm optimize. Track conversions with TikTok Pixel. TikTok Ads offer UK businesses a unique opportunity to reach a demographic that is increasingly avoiding traditional advertising channels.",
