    "title": "Local Listing Optimization: Getting Your UK Business Found Online",
    "excerpt": "Optimize your local business listings across platforms to maximize visibility in the UK search results.",
    "content": "## Beyond Google Business Profile\n\nWhile GBP is the most important local listing, UK businesses should optimize across multiple platforms. Facebook Business Pages, Instagram Business profiles, LinkedIn Company Pages, and Bing Places all contribute to your local search presence. Each platform sends signals to Google about your business's legitimacy and relevance. A comprehensive local listing strategy covers all major and UK-Specific platforms.\n\n## Optimization Checklist\n\nEnsure NAP (Name, Address, Phone) consistency across every listing. Even minor differences — \"St\" vs \"Street\" or \"+234\" vs \"0\" — can confuse search engines. Write complete descriptions that include services, keywords, and location information. Add high-quality photos to every profile. Select the most accurate categories. Include your business hours and update them for holidays. Add your website URL and any relevant service area information. For London businesses with multiple locations, create separate listings for each branch.\n\n## Monitoring and Maintenance\n\nUse tools like Moz Local, Yext, or BrightLocal to monitor your listings across platforms. Set up Google Alerts for your business name to catch new mentions. Respond to reviews and questions on all platforms, not just Google. Update listings promptly when information changes — moving to a new Kensington office or changing phone numbers. Regular maintenance of your local listings ensures customers can find accurate information wherever they search, reducing friction and increasing trust.",
