    "excerpt": "A breakdown of website costs in the UK, from basic brochure sites to custom web applications, plus ongoing expenses to budget for.",
    "content": "## How Much Does a Website Cost in the UK?\n\nOne of the most common questions businesses ask is: how much does a website cost?\n\nThe answer depends on your needs.\n\n## Typical Website Costs in the UK\n\n### Basic Brochure Website\n\n£500 – £2,000\n\nIdeal for small businesses needing a simple online presence.\n\n### Business Website\n\n£2,000 – £5,000\n\nIncludes custom design, SEO setup, and more advanced features.\n\n### E-commerce Website\n\n£2,500 – £10,000+\n\nDepends on product quantity, payment systems, and integrations.\n\n### Custom Web Applications\n\n£5,000+\n\nFor businesses needing unique functionality.\n\n## Ongoing Costs\n\n* Domain name: £10–£20/year\n* Hosting: £50–£500/year\n* Maintenance: £30–£200/month\n* SEO: Varies depending on competition\n\n## What Affects Cost?\n\n* Number of pages\n* Custom features\n* Design complexity\n* SEO requirements\n* Content creation\n\n## Final Thoughts\n\nA website should be viewed as an investment, not just a cost. The right website can generate leads and revenue for years.",
